# yocto-kas-rpi0-2w

Custom Linux images for Raspberry Pi Zero 2W — for people who enjoy watching progress bars

This project uses [Kas](https://kas.readthedocs.io/) to build a minimal Yocto-based Linux image for Raspberry Pi Zero 2W with USB gadget networking support. The image includes dropbear SSH server, busybox, and USB network gadget driver pre-configured.

Target machine: `raspberrypi0-2w-usbgadget`

## Prerequisites

- Git
- For Ubuntu: `pip install kas` + required packages (see [Dockerfile](./Dockerfile))
- For non-supported distros: Docker

## Supported Distributions

### Ubuntu

```bash
# Install required packages (see Dockerfile for full list)
sudo apt install build-essential chrpath cpio debianutils diffstat file gawk gcc git iputils-ping libacl1 locales python3 python3-git python3-jinja2 python3-pexpect python3-pip python3-subunit socat texinfo unzip wget xz-utils zstd bmap-tools

# Install kas
pip install kas

# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/BenesAdam/yocto-kas-rpi0-2w
cd yocto-kas-rpi0-2w

# Build the image
kas build kas.yml
```

### Non-Supported Distributions (Arch Linux, Fedora, etc.)

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/BenesAdam/yocto-kas-rpi0-2w
cd yocto-kas-rpi0-2w

# Build the Docker image (one time only)
./docker-build.sh

# Build via Docker
./build.sh
```

## Usage

```bash
# Build the image (Docker-based)
./build.sh

# Build the image (native - Ubuntu only)
kas build kas.yml

# Enter interactive shell (for debugging)
./config.sh

# Deploy to SD card (run on host)
./deploy.sh

# SSH to device
./ssh.sh
```

## Image Output

Built images are located in:
```
build/tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi0-2w-usbgadget/my-image.wic.bz2
```

## Flashing

```bash
# Extract and flash with bmaptool (recommended)
bmaptool copy build/tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi0-2w-usbgadget/my-image.wic.bz2 /dev/sdX

# Or use dd
bzcat build/tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi0-2w-usbgadget/my-image.wic.bz2 | sudo dd of=/dev/sdX bs=4M status=progress
```

## Network

The image configures USB gadget networking (RNDIS):
- Device IP: 192.168.7.2
- Host IP: 192.168.7.1
- Interface on host: USB Ethernet (check `ip link`)

## SSH Access

- User: root
- Password: (empty)
- IP: 192.168.7.2

```bash
ssh root@192.168.7.2
```

## Custom Recipes

This project includes custom recipes in `recipes-apps/`:
- `blink/` - LED blink demo
- `usb-gadget-network/` - USB network gadget configuration

And in `recipes-core/images/`:
- `my-image.bb` - Custom image definition

## Build Time

First build can take **several hours** depending on your CPU and internet connection. Subsequent builds are much faster thanks to shared state cache (sstate-cache).

## System Requirements

- **RAM**: Minimum 8GB recommended (16GB preferred)
- **Disk**: Minimum 100GB free space (for downloads, tmp, and sstate-cache)

## Shared State Cache

To speed up rebuilds, you can use a shared state cache:

```bash
# Add to local.conf or via kas environment
SSTATE_DIR = "/path/to/shared/sstate-cache"
```

## Version

- Yocto Project: whinlatter (5.3)
- BitBake: 2.16
- Poky: 5.3.3

## Troubleshooting

### "dubious ownership" git error
```bash
git config --global --add safe.directory '*'
```

### Build fails with missing dependencies
Make sure all required packages are installed (see Ubuntu section)

### Image too large
Check `IMAGE_ROOTFS_SIZE` in local.conf

